page.title: 09ECOLOGY
page.content: Around Wrestlingworth village many wild flowers are still to be found. On a survey taken during June alongside the Plantation and a field of oilseed rape, we found and identified, the following plants. Common Poppy; Buttercup; Bladder Campion; Fat Hen; Common Mallow; Clover; Wild Strawberry; Rosebay Willowherb; Bittersweet; Sorrel; Hopbine; Forget-me-not; White Bryony; Bindweed; Fieldspeedwell; Plantain; Nipplewort and Pineappleweed. During the spring, cowslips can be seen and away by the field sides a few clumps of violets are hidden away.
